        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 10:50PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 1050 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Scott, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Scott, Marmaton, Redfield, Richards, Hiattville, Devon, and
Garland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
